value: By playing the first X move, O was forced to block. Then, I recognized that, with my second move, I could force O to block while setting up an open ended row of four with my third move. This guaranteed my victory on my fourth move.

Blocking. Based on the moves already completed and taking into account the sequence of X/O turn a logical pattern begins to develop of the odds of x winning. The last quiz was heading towards a draw due to playing myself. The odds of x winning would only increase if a blunder or mistake is made.
